 (parent stretch border size)‚Üźopts ‚éēVGET'parent'('stretch'(1 0))('border' 0)('size'_size) ‚ćĚ Obtain named parameters

 ‚ćĚ If needed, modify or prepend a default 'where' for object creation
 (‚ąÜwhere ‚ąÜsize ‚ąÜextent)‚Üź‚ąä¬®((1‚Üď¬®arg),‚äā‚ć¨)[actions‚ć≥'where' 'size' 'extent'] ‚ćĚ Which of our defaults are they giving us anyway (so we can skip adding defaults)
 :If 4‚Č†‚ČĘwhere‚Üź‚ąÜwhere ‚ćĚ If they're not giving us a full 4‚ćī "where", generate a default they can modify later
     (psize pscale)‚Üźparent ‚éēVGET'_size' '_scale' ‚ćĚ What's the parent's size & scale? ‚ćĚ? Does this give us the right data for scale=0?
     punits‚Üź‚äÉ##.Classes._supp.MyUnits parent ‚ćĚ Get the unit-conversions for the parent object's scale
     :If 2‚Č†‚ČĘextent‚Üź‚ąÜextent ‚ćĚ Use an extent they gave us if we have one, otherwise calculate it
         extent‚Üźsize√óunits[1;]√∑punits ‚ćĚ Compute an extent using parent's scale
     :EndIf
     Borders‚Üź##.Classes._supp.GetBorders(_Class:from ‚čĄ _border:border)
     where_extent‚Üźextent+punits√∑‚ć®+/2 2‚ćīBorders[1;3;] ‚ćĚ Add border-spacing between extent and where
     :If 2=‚ČĘwhere ‚ćĚ If they've supplied a partial 'where' (2‚ćī), then just modify it in-place to append the extent to it
